Defendant Danesha T Radford in court with attorney Sergio Magana.  Defendant Danesha T Radford in custody.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
On State's motion, Court ordered COUNT 1 REPEATER PENALTY ENHANCER  DISMISSED BUT READ IN.
On State's motion, Court ordered COUNT 2 DISMISSED BUT READ IN.
AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised she is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised she is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 7 YEARS, with credit for 78 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4 YEARS.  The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program .
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions:  
*Serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction;
*AODA assessment and follow through with recommended programming; 
*Maintain absolute sobriety with random urine screens.
Defendant to complete a parenting and nuturing class.  Defendant to cooperate with Children's Court Orders.
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs over the duration of probation failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges by over the duration of probation or, if not paid, a civil judgment is ordered.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended and she may not vote in any election until her civil rights are restored. 
